  "notes": "Per-hole distances and pars verified identical across three sources: the current official GNK Golf scorecard PDF (June 2022), the club's own website scorecard PDF (hrgs.es, 2018 edition), and mscorecard.com. All internal checks pass: pars sum to 72 (36+36), men's and ladies' SI are each permutations of 1-18, and every tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its printed total (6356/5854/5552/5084 m). Stroke index uses the current GNK card's Hcp Caballeros row; the older 2018 club-site card printed a different single HCP allocation (1:4, 2:11, 3:3, 4:14, 5:9, 6:16, 7:8, 8:15, 9:1, 10:18, 11:5, 12:17, 13:10, 14:6, 15:13, 16:7, 17:12, 18:2) - the 2022 card supersedes it. Ladies' SI on the 2022 card (if needed): 12,6,10,4,18,8,16,14,2,11,3,17,9,1,13,7,15,5. Ratings (Vc/Slope) are from the current official card: men Blancas 73.5/139, Amarillas 70.8/132, Azules 69.3/124, Rojas 66.6/118; two ladies' ratings 76.1/139 and 72.7/133 are printed without explicit tee labels - assigned to Azules and Rojas respectively, consistent with the RFEG legacy rating set (Azules Damas 76.0/137, Rojas Damas rated). Note: the RFEG club page still lists an older rating set (Blancas 74.0/143, Amarillas 70.9/135, Azules 69.3/125, plus discontinued Verdes 5226 m and an older shorter Rojas at 4679 m) that predates the current card; the current club/GNK card was preferred."
